you can always up this ratio to fit your needs, if you do not care about being a "pureist" in the reality of <abbr title="Umbra Space Industries (a collection of mods)">USI</abbr>.  either make the inputs less or the output higher, or both....   depending on where you wish to make the changes.   Lower inputs mean less mining for the same output, higher output will mean more output for the same ammount of mining.  so just decide where you want the "bonus" to be and change this value.  

you can do this in the file directly, or with a <abbr title="Module Manager (mod)">MM</abbr> patch if you do not want to change the default files.

GameData\UmbraSpaceIndustries\LifeSupport\LSModule.cfg

    @PART[MiniISRU]
    {MODULE{	name = ModuleResourceConverter_USI	ConverterName = Fertilizer	StartActionName = Start ISRU [Ore -> Fertilizer]	StopActionName = Stop ISRU [Ore -> Fertilizer]INPUT_RESOURCE	{		ResourceName = Ore		Ratio = 2.5	}	INPUT_RESOURCE	{		ResourceName = ElectricCharge		Ratio = 30	}	OUTPUT_RESOURCE	{		ResourceName = Fertilizer		Ratio = 0.0025		DumpExcess = False	}}	
    }
